				"narration": {
					"tone": "product explainer, opening",
					"pause_ms": 140,
					"text": "Lambda calculus gave computing its theoretical foundation. Church and Turing showed that pure functions and sequential evaluation define what is computable. But the model assumes a single thread of control with no primitives for concurrency, distribution, or communication channels."
